acf.description:
Finding yourself in Nihonmachi—Japantown in Japanese—is one of the most authentic experiences of San Francisco. Culture radiates from this vibrant 6-block neighborhood and its original character prevails, even in the face of historic challenges.

Locals and tourists alike are hard pressed to find a dull moment. Explore the streets, plazas, landmarks, and spiritual centers. Explore blocks of Victorian homes as an architecture buff, hidden dining experiences as a foodie, and satiate your fashionista vibes with a one-of-a-kind shopping spree. Whether renting a kimono at Asakichi, getting your ramen fix at Marufuku Ramen, celebrating the Cherry Blossom Festival, or giving your mind and body a little TLC from Kabuki Springs and Spa, you’ll find your vibe in Japantown.

posts.title: Bao Bei
posts.description: Bao Bei is a unique restaurant in Chinatown that cultivates casual intimate dining experiences by providing small plates meant to be shared amongst a group of friends and family. Influences are taken from Taiwan and Shanghai but we are also inspired by a range of global flavours that form a more modern approach to Chinese cooking. We also love a good stiff cocktail and a nice glass of pinot noir to go with our food so we’ve taken great care to create distinctive libations and to curate a nice little list of wines for you.
